According to the official World Milk Day website, this special day was established in 2001 by the Food and Agriculture Organisation of the United Nations, to recognize the importance of milk as a global food, and to celebrate the dairy sector.  There are countless recipes all over the world that make use of milk as an important ingredient, and over the years many different types of milk alternatives have been created and perfected for people with particular dietary requirements and preferences. To celebrate this World Milk Day, recreate one of these delicious, quick and easy milk based recipes which you and your loved ones will be sure to love.  For the water roux For the yeast mixture  For the dough:  This recipe was found on kwokspots.com ALSO READ: 5 delicious and hearty recipes to recreate using mixed vegetables This recipe was found on acouplecooks.com This recipe was found on jamieoliver.com